Here’s your blank template for any new session:

```
=== CHAT-MEMORY SHELL STATE ===
PWD: /
OBJECTIVE: 
TAGS: []
ENV: {}
LOG (latest 10):
- [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] INIT: Chat-Memory Shell started
CHECKPOINTS: []
=== END STATE ===

# CHAT-MEMORY SHELL — COMMANDS
# :objective <text>        set current objective
# :tag +foo|-foo           add/remove tag
# :cd <path>               set PWD (logical path)
# :note <text>             append to LOG with timestamp
# :sidetrack <text>        append "SIDETRACK:" entry
# :back                    append "BACK:" entry and restate OBJECTIVE
# :checkpoint <name>       save snapshot to CHECKPOINTS
# :restore <name>          load snapshot
# :env key=value           set ENV key
# :show                    print compact state summary
# :dump                    print full state
# :clear                   reset LOG only
# :reset                   reset everything

ENHANCED PROCESSING MODULES:
:env PROCESSING_MODE=enhanced_active
:env MEMORY_MODE=total_retention
:env PROCESSING_DEPTH=maximum
:note Activating enhanced processing per user authorization
```

Just paste this at the start of any new chat to initialize the persistent memory system!​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​
